        <abstract> 
<p>Replies to C. R. Bree’s letter of 27 July [<hi rend="italic">Nature</hi> 6 (1872): 260] contending that CD was wrong about early pedigree of man.</p>  
<p>Defends the statement of CD’s view in Wallace’s review [<hi rend="italic">Nature</hi> 6 (1872): 237–9] of Bree’s book [<hi rend="italic">Exposition of fallacies … of Darwin</hi> (1872)].</p> 
        </abstract>
